  {

   "id": "d2181b35",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from Anis_TTF_rays import ALI_FMM\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "\n",
    "matplotlib.rc('text', usetex=True) # allows using latex for labels in plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "100158ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Define distance between points in grid and the source/reciever locations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "be601fa6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dnx = 1e-3\n",
    "scx = dnx * np.array([1, 199])\n",
    "scz = dnx * np.array([30, 180])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ae3fcfb8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Create matrices for material properties. veln is the anisotropic orientation of the material, velpn is the material index of the material (by defalt material 1 is isotropic with velocity 1 if no materials are imput) and vel_map is a velocity scaling parameter (if using defalt materials these values are the velocity at each point. We create a velocity gradient from 3000 to 7200."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "3589ebc2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "veln = 0 * np.ones((201, 201))\n",
    "velpn = 1 * np.ones((201, 201), dtype=int)\n",
    "vel_map = np.zeros((201, 201))\n",
    "for i in range(veln.shape[0]):\n",
    "    for j in range(veln.shape[1]):\n",
    "        vel_map[i, j] = 3000 + 21 * j"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "55ef2555",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Defining materials using stiffness tensors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "53a4a158",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Define material properties using stifness tensors (in Pa) and density values (in Kg/$\\textrm{m}^3$) for materials with stifness matrix in the form \n",
    "$$ c = \\begin{pmatrix}\n",
    "c_{11} & c_{12} & c_{13} & 0 & 0 & 0\\\\\n",
    "c_{12} & c_{22} & c_{23} & 0 & 0 & 0\\\\\n",
    "c_{13} & c_{23} & c_{33} & 0 & 0 & 0\\\\\n",
    "0 & 0 & 0 & c_{44} & 0 & 0\\\\\n",
    "0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & c_{55} & 0\\\\\n",
    "0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & c_{66}\n",
    "\\end{pmatrix} $$\n",
    "Velocities in the y,z plane only dependant on stifness tensors $c_{22}$, $c_{23}$, $c_{33}$, $c_{44}$ and the density $\\sigma$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "c5c72028",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "c_22 = 249.0e9\n",
    "c_23 = 133.0e9\n",
    "c_33 = 205.0e9\n",
    "c_44 = 125.0e9\n",
    "sigma = 7850\n",
    "\n",
    "c_22 = 2.036e11\n",
    "c_23 = 1.298e11\n",
    "c_33 = 2.036e11\n",
    "c_44 = 1.335e11\n",
    "sigma = 7874\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a2dc8e06",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Define veln(anisotropic orientation), velpn(material index), vel_map(velocity scaling), transducer location and initialise class"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "5843c0bc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "veln = 0 * np.ones((201, 201))\n",
    "velpn = 1 * np.ones(veln.shape, dtype=int)\n",
    "vel_map = 1 * np.ones(veln.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "scx = dnx * np.array([1, 199])\n",
    "scz = dnx * np.array([100, 140])\n",
    "\n",
    "Forward_Model_1 = ALI_FMM(veln, velpn, vel_map, scx, scz, dnx=1e-3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a5862d5f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plot group and phase velocity curves using stifness tensors and density. Two materials are then defined and added to defalt material. Defalt material(isotropic) has material index of 1 and two added materials have indices of 2 and 3."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "2e059699",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

      ]
     },

     },

    },
    {
     "data": {

       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "material id's of new materials are 2 - 3\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Forward_Model_1.generate_group_vel(c_22, c_23, c_33, c_44, sigma)\n",
    "Forward_Model_1.generate_phase_vel(c_22, c_23, c_33, c_44, sigma)\n",
    "\n",
    "materials = np.array([[c_22, c_23, c_33, c_44, 2 * sigma], [c_22, c_23, c_33, c_44, 3 * sigma]])\n",
    "Forward_Model_1.add_materials(materials, True) # True used here to keep all previous materials"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "498307f3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "All materials are removed(add True as second argument to keep previous materials) and new material is added(with material id of 1)."
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 24,

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3bef9b0f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Solving christoffel equation during run time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "90c39daa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Define material properties. Here we give a matrix for the material properties at each point in the grid with stifness tensors in MPa. Here the stiffness tensors must be defined as 64 bit integers. The christoffel equation will be solved during run time. The material index is set to 0 when using stiffness tensors and density (alows us to use a mixture of velocity curves and stifness tensors). velocity scaling (vel_map) set to 1 when using stifness tensors and density (velocitys can be scaled using density)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "2027b037",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "c_22 = 249.0e9\n",
    "c_23 = 133.0e9\n",
    "c_33 = 205.0e9\n",
    "c_44 = 125.0e9\n",
    "sigma = 7850\n",
    "stif_density = np.zeros((veln.shape[0], veln.shape[1], 5), dtype=np.int64)  # Stiffness tensors and density for all grid points in order c_22, c_23, c_33 and c_44\n",
    "# Stiffness tensors in MPa due to 64bit limitations\n",
    "stif_density[:, :, 0] = (c_22 / 1000000) * np.ones(veln.shape, dtype=np.int64)\n",
    "stif_density[:, :, 1] = (c_23 / 1000000) * np.ones(veln.shape, dtype=np.int64)\n",
    "stif_density[:, :, 2] = (c_33 / 1000000) * np.ones(veln.shape, dtype=np.int64)\n",
    "stif_density[:, :, 3] = (c_44 / 1000000) * np.ones(veln.shape, dtype=np.int64)\n",
    "stif_density[:, :, 4] = sigma * np.ones(veln.shape, dtype=np.int64)\n",
    "\n",
    "veln = 20 * np.ones(veln.shape)\n",
    "velpn = 0 * np.ones(veln.shape, dtype=int)\n",
    "vel_map = 1 * np.ones(veln.shape)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "949e4b5c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Define transducer locations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "968365e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scx = dnx * np.array([1, 199, 100])\n",
    "scz = dnx * np.array([100, 140, 1])"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "83002705",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "2137ce5b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

   ]

  },

   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
